snippet.textDisplay:
5G is killing bees, and MKBHD found that it basically only works 30ft in line of sight from a 5G pole. Top it off with cellular and broadband companies wanting to launch 35,000 satellites which basically will block/distort the view of our night sky. Astronomers are especially mad because of the reflections shone through telescopes. Imagine missing out on rare events or a meteor shower because there's thousands of reflective satellites being launched in space. I'm all for innovation, but not at the careless expense of wasting Earth's natural resources.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X5IhKHGDKhM
